{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8ba0153c-0fda-4b8c-8e64-cacbd54cfe5f","content":"**Starting with MSTest.Sdk 4.0.0, the VSTest compatibility layer (`vstest.console`, `dotnet test` via VSTest) is disabled by default.** The SDK now assumes you're using Microsoft.Testing.Platform (the new `dotnet test` integration) exclusively.\n\nThis means `vstest.console.exe` can no longer discover or run tests from assemblies built with MSTest.Sdk ≥ 4.0.\n\n### Your options:\n\n1. **Re-enable the VSTest bridge** by adding this to your `.csproj`:\n\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformVSTestBridge>true</EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformVSTestBridge>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n2. **Migrate your CI to use `dotnet test`** (which now routes through Microsoft.Testing.Platform directly), or invoke the test executable directly:\n\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test TestProject.csproj\n   # or run the compiled executable directly:\n   ./TestProject --list-tests\n   ```\n\nOption 2 is the recommended long-term path since VSTest is being phased out. Would you like me to update your project file or CI pipeline?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1ad07c17-adb5-4043-b4cd-ae9656ad2ec0","outputTokens":291,"requestId":"BC25:35F104:229CB17:2690492:69FAAB7A"},"id":"6cdb6fa9-d06a-4973-8664-930436d43e6f","timestamp":"2026-05-06T02:46:26.468Z","parentId":"c38d31ae-bc22-49ab-89f7-4c5021969272"}
